      "text": [
        " اَلصَّادِقُ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"مَنِ اُضْطُرَّ إِلَى اَلْمَيْتَةِ وَ اَلدَّمِ وَ لَحْمِ اَلْخِنْزِيرِ فَلَمْ يَأْكُلْ شَيْئاً مِنْ ذَلِكَ حَتَّى يَمُوتَ فَهُوَ كَافِرٌ\""
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4214 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) said:\n\"Whoever is compelled by necessity to eat from a dead animal, blood, or the flesh of a pig, yet refrains from eating any of it until he dies, then he is considered a disbeliever.\""
        ]
      }
    },
